By Chinyere Omeire Lagos – A 27-year-old staffer of a fast food joint, Faruq Olanrewaju, who allegedly stole his employer’s N948, 500, was on, Tuesday, arraigned before an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court, Lagos. Olanrewaju was charged alongside a businesswoman, Queen Silas, 40, on a two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing. The defendants, who reside at No. 87, Aroloya Street, Off Adeniji Adele, Lagos Island and No. 31, Olayinwola Street, Oworoshoki, respectively, however, pleaded not guilty to the two-count charge preferred against them. The Prosecutor, Sgt. Chinedu Njoku, told the court that the defendants committed the offences between Nov. 30 and Dec. 10 at Bukka Hut in Lekki Phase I, Eti- Osa Local Government area of Lagos. “Olanrewaju, a staffer of Bukka Hut, connived with a businesswoman (Silas) and defrauded his employer of the sum of N948, 500,” the prosecutor said. According to him, the offences contravene Sections 287 (7) and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Sections 287 (7) and 411 provide seven years and two years jail terms respectively as punishments for offences of stealing and conspiracy. The Magistrate, Mrs Folashade Botoku, granted the defendants bail in the sum of N100,000 each, with two sureties each in like sum. Botoku said that the sureties must be gainfully employed and must show evidence of tax payment to the Lagos State Government. She also ordered that the addresses of the sureties must be verified. The case was adjourned till Jan. 24, 2020 for mention. (NAN)